#HYPERVISOR
## A hypervisor is also known as a virtual machine monitor or VMM. 
## It is a software layer that helps with the creation and management of virtual machines or VMs on a single hardware platform.
## It smartly manages and isolates computer's resources, for example its processing or memory so that each virtual machine can get what it needs. 
## It helps many operating systems run together securely and efficiently.
## Layman terms - A 'hypervisor' is basically a piece of software that lets you run multiple 'virtual machines or VMs all at one time on that single machine. The goal is to use the computer's power efficiently so that nothing sits idle.






